  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Sport climbing crag with routes graded 6–8. Routes can be top-roped.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:fjardhundra"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A sport climbing crag with routes in grades 6–8. Top-roping is possible.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "karaktar": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Character",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A mostly vertical wall, estimated to be 10–15 metres high. Enjoyable climbing on positive holds with good friction underfoot.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "historik-m-m": {
          "title": {
            "text": "History, etc.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Climbing began at the crag around 1993, but its real breakthrough probably came in the summer of 1995, when the first route guide was published. A number of further new routes were also put up in 1996 and 1997. Today there are 31 routes in total (including a couple of combinations/variations), put up by around ten different climbers.\n\nAs the crag became increasingly popular, Uppsala Klätterklubb installed several additional abseil anchors in 1998 and 1999, with substantial support from Crux AB. This was to avoid damaging the trees and vegetation above the crag, but above all to improve safety and increase climbing activity.\n\nNote!! The abseil anchors have carabiners with non-locking gates, which should be backed up with a locking carabiner when top-roping. They can become unclipped if the rope twists around itself or passes over the carabiner/anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Drive to Fjärdhundra. Continue through the village; after about a kilometre, cross a bridge and immediately turn left towards Altuna onto a gravel road. Follow this briefly, then turn right towards Nygård. The crag soon comes into view.\n\nPass the crag, continue past a handful of houses and then park on the left in the signed “Klätterparkering” climbing car park (the sign may have fallen down). Make sure you do not obstruct other traffic.\n\nA discussion of the directions can be found on Bloxc (http://www.bloxc.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1469). Also check here (http://www.utsidan.se/forum/showthread.php?t=43967). It appears to be a sensitive issue.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "access": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The landowner is positive towards climbing but does not want an invasion of climbers. Keep a low profile, park in the designated area and behave responsibly. Contact Uppsala Klätterklubb before visiting the crag for details of the access situation.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag consists of one long wall, divided here into three sections, with mossy areas between them. The sections and routes are listed from right to left, which is also the order in which they are reached on the approach.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "sodra-delen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Southern Section",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "akern": {
          "title": {
            "text": "The Field",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "skogen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "The Forest",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "fjardhundra-led-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start on the left-hand side of the chimney; the landing is a thorn bush to the right.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-3": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A short problem leading onto the ledge. Run-out to the finish.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-4": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A must-do among the easier routes.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-5": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Probably the most frequently climbed route at the crag. Sustained climbing on good holds.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-6": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Hard for the grade.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-7": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A good warm-up for those who prefer placing nuts and hexes. Best to avoid using cams behind the sharp blocks.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-8": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Hard (6a+?) start, with the first bolt placed quite high. A ‘beginner’s grade’, but not for beginners.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-9": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A good, sustained line.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-10": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A frequently climbed route.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-11": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A route with few repeats.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-12": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A route that enjoyed a renaissance after the new top anchor was installed.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-13": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Varied climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-14": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The route has also gone by the name Åttjäveln, perhaps because this part of the crag offers somewhat inconsistent climbing in places.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-15": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A little hard to read.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-16": {
          "description": {
            "text": "One of the better routes at the crag. A distinct crux sets the grade.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-17": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A good, sustained route. Keep up the pace.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-18": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Small, painful crimps. Joins no. 15 near the top.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-19": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Fat bolts!!",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-20": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Named after a slithering animal that reportedly enjoyed sheltering beneath a rope bag below the route.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-21": {
          "description": {
            "text": "NB: Do not climb onto Huggormen.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-22": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A slightly harder finishing variation to no. 20.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-23": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A somewhat delicate start followed by relatively good climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-24": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Frequently repeated, with a fair number of onsights to its name.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-25": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A direct start straight over the small roof, raising the grade slightly.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-26": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Here, at least, you can put your presumed indoor-wall skills to use.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-27": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A combination following no. 23 to the second bolt, then moving onto no. 25.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-28": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A crux-focused route.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-29": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Delicate slab climbing in places.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-31": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Once the somewhat high first bolt is clipped, you can enjoy some good climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-32": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A small nut or cam can be useful at the start.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        },
        "fjardhundra-led-34": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Once fine, clean climbing. Protects adequately with two Camalot 1s or a couple of smaller cams, a medium-sized nut and a WC 1 cam.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:fjardhundra"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
